data.title: Wax Museum (Jay and the Americans album)
data.text:
1970 studio album by Jay and The Americans

Wax MuseumStudio album by ReleasedFebruary 28, 1970RecordedA&R Studios, New York CityGenrePopLabelUnited ArtistsProducerJay and the Americans, Thomas KayeJay and The Americans chronologySingles from Wax Museum, Vol. 1

Released: November 1969

Professional ratingsReview scoresSourceRatingAllmusic[1]

Wax Museum is the eighth studio album by Jay and the Americans released on February 28, 1970. The album went to #105 on the Billboard 200 chart, reached #68 on the Cashbox chart,[2] and #71 in Canada.[3] The album was the group's last charting album.

The group's cover of The Ronettes' song "Walkin' in the Rain" hit #19 on the Billboard Hot 100 in 1970,[4] and #17 in Canada.[5]
